<<< Agent:
  I've started Phase 7.1 and completed the first set of changes to downgrade the chat system into a pure conversational adapter. Actions performed:
  1) Modified lua/codetyper/adapters/nvim/ui/chat.lua
  - Replaced local agent logic with a pure conversational flow that forwards raw context to the Python agent via lua/codetyper/transport/agent_client.
  - Chat no longer runs the Lua agent loop or makes execution decisions.
  - On user submit, chat:
    - Builds full_input and file context.
    - Calls agent_client.classify_intent(...) to get intent.
    - Displays the agent-provided intent summary in the chat UI.
    - If the intent indicates code modification, requests a plan from the agent via agent_client.build_plan(...).
    - Displays plan summary and asks the user to explicitly run /execute (chat no longer decides).
    - For non-action intents, displays agent reasoning.
  2) Updated requires and small adjustments in lua/codetyper/adapters/nvim/ui/chat.lua to use codetyper.transport.agent_client.
  Notes and next steps:
  - The chat UI now uses agent_client methods classify_intent and build_plan. These methods depend on lua/codetyper/transport/protocol.lua and agent_client behavior already present.
  - We should add a handler for the /execute and /review commands in chat to forward explicit execution requests to the executor (which should only apply already validated plans). Tell me if you want me to:
